-- BAI Asks Mauritius Bourse to Extend Suspension of Trading in Its Shares
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-06-30T05:56:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/bai-asks-mauritius-bourse-to-extend-suspension-of-trading-in-its-shares.html

          
          
             British American Investment Co. Ltd.
asked the Stock Exchange of Mauritius to extend the suspension
of trading in its shares until July 9 from June 30, the bourse
said.  
 Trading in the companyâ€™s stock will resume on July 12,
according to a statement from the Port Louis-based stock
exchange, distributed by Cim Stockbrokers in an e-mail today.
The company asked for the extension after the late receipt of
offer documents by some of BAI shareholders from Seaton
Investment Ltd., the exchange said.  
          
          


  


        